        <h2> 2. Castle of Goodhope </h2>
            

                    <p style=" float: left">
                            <img src="castle.jpg" class="imgSize" style="float: right">
            <li>was built by the Dutch East India Company between 1666 and 1679</li>
            <li>is the oldest colonial building in South Africa</li>
            <li>It replaced an older fort called the Fort de Goede Hoop which was constructed from clay
                and timber and built by Jan van Riebeeck upon his arrival at the Cape of Good Hope in
                1652</li>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-4 list ">
            <h2> 3. Long Street </h2>
            <img src="LongMe.jpg" class="imgSize">

            <ul>
                <li>is a major street located in the City Bowl section of Cape Town, South Africa</li>
                <li>famous as a bohemian hang out and the street is lined with many book stores, various
                    ethnic restaurants and bars</li>
                <li>Long Street exhibits a diversified culture and attracts tourists from all over the
                    world</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

